1
00:00:00,310 --> 00:00:07,149
CHAPTER ONE
At the Golden Globes

2
00:00:07,149 --> 00:00:15,740
Jack Morgan got out of his dark blue Lamborghini
near the Beverly Hilton.

3
00:00:15,740 --> 00:00:26,539
It was the night of the Golden Globes, and
he was with a beautiful and famous movie star.

4
00:00:26,539 --> 00:00:34,690
He helped Guinevere Scott-Evans out of the
car, and she held his hand hard.

5
00:00:34,690 --> 00:00:43,830
Guinevere trusted Jack, and she trusted his
company, Private.

6
00:00:43,830 --> 00:00:48,870
Everyone trusted Private; it was the best.

7
00:00:48,870 --> 00:00:58,490
But then Jack's oldest friend, Andy Cushman,
called him.

8
00:00:58,490 --> 00:01:01,140
Andy spoke quickly.

9
00:01:01,140 --> 00:01:04,870
"Jack, come to my house now!

10
00:01:04,870 --> 00:01:08,100
I need you."

11
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:11,549
"It's not a good time.

12
00:01:11,549 --> 00:01:16,170
What's wrong?" asked Jack.

13
00:01:16,170 --> 00:01:18,490
"It's Shelby.

14
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:23,409
She's dead," said Andy.

15
00:01:23,409 --> 00:01:27,759
Shelby and Andy married six months ago.

16
00:01:27,759 --> 00:01:35,770
Guinevere wasn't happy, but Jack took her
to her table.

17
00:01:35,770 --> 00:01:41,950
Then, he was on the road to Andy's house in
Bluffs.

18
00:01:41,950 --> 00:01:49,939
He stopped near the open front door, took
out his gun, and went in.

19
00:01:49,939 --> 00:01:54,039
"Andy?" shouted Jack.

20
00:01:54,039 --> 00:01:55,850
"Jack!

21
00:01:55,850 --> 00:01:59,490
I'm in the bedroom."

22
00:01:59,490 --> 00:02:05,549
Jack went through the house, his gun in his
hand.

23
00:02:05,549 --> 00:02:11,200
In the bedroom, there were clothes everywhere.

24
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:16,819
Shelby was on the bed, with blood on her head.

25
00:02:16,819 --> 00:02:22,340
"What happened?" asked Jack.

26
00:02:22,340 --> 00:02:27,180
Andy was near Shelby, his head in his hands.

27
00:02:27,180 --> 00:02:29,950
"Someone shot her.

28
00:02:29,950 --> 00:02:33,950
Please find him!"

29
00:02:33,950 --> 00:02:37,480
Jack took photos of everything in the room.

30
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:42,330
"Did you call the police?" he asked.

31
00:02:42,330 --> 00:02:47,870
"No, I wanted you here," said Andy.

32
00:02:47,870 --> 00:02:53,950
"Do you have a gun?" asked Jack.

33
00:02:53,950 --> 00:02:57,130
"No," said Andy.

34
00:02:57,130 --> 00:03:01,569
"OK, you must understand.

35
00:03:01,569 --> 00:03:05,560
The police will want to talk to you.

36
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:09,750
They always want it to be easy.

37
00:03:09,750 --> 00:03:17,040
They will think, 'A woman is dead - did her
husband kill her?'

38
00:03:17,040 --> 00:03:21,870
But I can help," said Jack.

39
00:03:21,870 --> 00:03:29,450
He called the police and waited for them to
arrive.

40
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:33,200
CHAPTER TWO
A young woman dies

41
00:03:33,200 --> 00:03:40,769
Justine worked with Jack at Private.

42
00:03:40,769 --> 00:03:44,120
People trusted her, too.

43
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:50,590
Tonight, she was in an expensive Italian restaurant.

44
00:03:50,590 --> 00:03:54,370
Then, the chief of police called her.

45
00:03:54,370 --> 00:04:01,720
"Another young woman is dead," Justine told
her friend.

46
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:03,010
"I must go."

47
00:04:03,010 --> 00:04:11,370
In two years, eleven young women in Los Angeles
were dead.

48
00:04:11,370 --> 00:04:13,569
Now, it was twelve.

49
00:04:13,569 --> 00:04:23,620
The killer always took something from the
women - hair, a necklace, clothes.

50
00:04:23,620 --> 00:04:33,490
Then, the killer emailed the chief of police
and told him about the women's things.

51
00:04:33,490 --> 00:04:46,110
Nobody knew where the emails came from, but
the emails all had the same name - Steemcleena.

52
00:04:46,110 --> 00:04:54,110
The police found the women's things, but they
couldn't find Steemcleena.

53
00:04:54,110 --> 00:05:02,500
The police wanted Justine, and Private, to
help them find the killer.

54
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:11,720
Emilio Cruz, from Private, stopped his Mercedes
at the restaurant door, and Justine got in.

55
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:19,090
"What do you know about this girl?" asked
Justine.

56
00:05:19,090 --> 00:05:23,520
"Her name is Connie Yu.

57
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:29,370
She was sixteen and very intelligent," said
Emilio.

58
00:05:29,370 --> 00:05:34,789
"She was on the ground behind a restaurant.

59
00:05:34,789 --> 00:05:38,270
There was an earring in her left ear.

60
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:43,050
There was no right ear."

61
00:05:43,050 --> 00:05:49,690
Emilio stopped in a small, dark street near
some police cars.

62
00:05:49,690 --> 00:05:54,620
They walked past the police and spoke to the
doctor.

63
00:05:54,620 --> 00:06:04,660
"We'll get an email about the ear in a day
or two," Emilio said.

64
00:06:04,660 --> 00:06:10,850
At 2 a.m., Justine and Emilio were at Private's
offices.

65
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:17,009
They talked to Sci, Private's forensic expert.

66
00:06:17,009 --> 00:06:23,220
"We have the woman's bag and cell phone,"
said Justine.

67
00:06:23,220 --> 00:06:27,360
"Can you look for DNA on them?"

68
00:06:27,360 --> 00:06:38,300
"Of course," said Sci. "I can work all night
on it."

69
00:06:38,300 --> 00:06:40,840
CHAPTER THREE
At Private

70
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:54,960
The next morning, Justine, Emilio, Sci, and
Mo-bot, the computer expert, were in the office.

71
00:06:54,960 --> 00:07:01,870
Jack opened his laptop and showed them the
photos from Andy's bedroom.

72
00:07:01,870 --> 00:07:05,520
"Look at these," he said.

73
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:10,110
"I can't see anything important.

74
00:07:10,110 --> 00:07:11,110
Can you?"

75
00:07:11,110 --> 00:07:19,280
"Did the killer take anything from the house?"
asked Justine.

76
00:07:19,280 --> 00:07:24,340
"No, he took nothing," said Jack.

77
00:07:24,340 --> 00:07:33,000
"And were Andy and Shelby happy together?"
asked Emilio.

78
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:36,930
"Yes," said Jack.

79
00:07:36,930 --> 00:07:39,550
"Very happy."

80
00:07:39,550 --> 00:07:41,810
"OK," said Justine.

81
00:07:41,810 --> 00:07:45,610
"This killer is a professional.

82
00:07:45,610 --> 00:07:49,570
But why did he kill Shelby?"

83
00:07:49,570 --> 00:07:54,430
"The police always like easy answers.

84
00:07:54,430 --> 00:08:01,919
They will think one thing: Andy killed her,"
said Emilio.

85
00:08:01,919 --> 00:08:05,280
"Did Andy kill her?"

86
00:08:05,280 --> 00:08:09,390
"No, he didn't," said Jack.

87
00:08:09,390 --> 00:08:12,039
"I know Andy well.

88
00:08:12,039 --> 00:08:13,990
He loved Shelby."

89
00:08:13,990 --> 00:08:18,760
"What next?" asked Mo-bot.

90
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:25,290
"We look at Andy and Shelby," said Jack.

91
00:08:25,290 --> 00:08:31,259
"We talk to their friends and to people they
work with.

92
00:08:31,259 --> 00:08:33,409
Let's go."

93
00:08:33,409 --> 00:08:36,110
"Wait!" said Justine.

94
00:08:36,110 --> 00:08:41,250
"I have some news on the young woman.

95
00:08:41,250 --> 00:08:43,760
We have her bag.

96
00:08:43,760 --> 00:08:52,640
Sci couldn't find any new DNA, but Mo-bot
looked at her phone."

97
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:58,130
"I looked at the text messages," said Mo-bot.

98
00:08:58,130 --> 00:09:04,360
"There were hundreds, from twenty or thirty
people.

99
00:09:04,360 --> 00:09:11,310
I looked at the numbers, and they are all
friends or family.

100
00:09:11,310 --> 00:09:17,631
But there is one strange message - I can't
get the number for it.

101
00:09:17,631 --> 00:09:18,631
Look!"

102
00:09:18,631 --> 00:09:25,840
A text message came up on the wall.

103
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,670
Connie.

104
00:09:27,670 --> 00:09:29,610
It's Linda.

105
00:09:29,610 --> 00:09:32,060
My mom took my phone.

106
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:36,010
I must talk to you.

107
00:09:36,010 --> 00:09:38,300
Can we meet?

108
00:09:38,300 --> 00:09:39,970
Please!

109
00:09:39,970 --> 00:09:42,060
Behind the restaurant.

110
00:09:42,060 --> 00:09:45,570
At 8.30 p.m.

111
00:09:45,570 --> 00:09:47,420
Don't tell anyone.

112
00:09:47,420 --> 00:09:52,339
"I talked to Linda," said Mo-bot.

113
00:09:52,339 --> 00:09:57,480
"Her mother didn't take her phone.

114
00:09:57,480 --> 00:10:01,480
Linda didn't send that message.

115
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:09,389
The killer got into Connie's phone and found
all her friends.

116
00:10:09,389 --> 00:10:15,540
Then, he sent her that message from his phone."

117
00:10:15,540 --> 00:10:26,930
"But we can't find the number of the killer's
phone," said Sci. "It isn't possible."

118
00:10:26,930 --> 00:10:31,170
"Who is Steemcleena?"

119
00:10:31,170 --> 00:10:34,560
asked Jack.

120
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:42,950
Rudolph Crocker left his office at 7 p.m.
and went for a drink.

121
00:10:42,950 --> 00:10:49,310
At 9 p.m., he was at home and ready for a
run.

122
00:10:49,310 --> 00:10:55,910
He ran out to Marina del Rey and thought about
Connie Yu.

123
00:10:55,910 --> 00:10:59,810
That was a great evening.

124
00:10:59,810 --> 00:11:02,760
There was nobody near him.

125
00:11:02,760 --> 00:11:07,040
He stopped near a boat and put something on
it.

126
00:11:07,040 --> 00:11:14,860
Then, he went home and sent an email to the
Chief of Police.

127
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:23,910
You can find Connie Yu's ear on a boat in
Marina del Rey.

128
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:27,220
Steemcleena.

129
00:11:27,220 --> 00:11:33,470
CHAPTER FOUR
Another young woman

130
00:11:33,470 --> 00:11:39,790
Jason Pilser got a text message at work at
3 p.m.

131
00:11:39,790 --> 00:11:45,550
Scylla, your big night is Saturday.

132
00:11:45,550 --> 00:11:48,590
Be ready.

133
00:11:48,590 --> 00:11:50,110
Steemcleena.

134
00:11:50,110 --> 00:11:55,010
"Scylla" was Jason's computer name.

135
00:11:55,010 --> 00:12:01,290
At 6 p.m., he left his office and drove to
a store.

136
00:12:01,290 --> 00:12:06,300
He bought some gloves and some electric cable.

137
00:12:06,300 --> 00:12:12,339
He didn't pay with a card, and he looked down
at the ground.

138
00:12:12,339 --> 00:12:18,339
He didn't want the cameras in the store to
see him.

139
00:12:18,339 --> 00:12:21,920
The big night was in three days.

140
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:26,740
He was ready to kill his first woman.

141
00:12:26,740 --> 00:12:32,029
"I'm going for a walk!"

142
00:12:32,029 --> 00:12:36,600
Marguerite Esperanza shouted to her grandmother.

143
00:12:36,600 --> 00:12:39,730
It was Saturday evening.

144
00:12:39,730 --> 00:12:44,740
Marguerite walked out the house and on to
Rowena Avenue.

145
00:12:44,740 --> 00:12:48,860
A text message came on to her phone.

146
00:12:48,860 --> 00:12:51,270
Hi Marg.

147
00:12:51,270 --> 00:12:52,950
It's Lamar.

148
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:55,839
Where are you?

149
00:12:55,839 --> 00:12:58,540
She read it and answered.

150
00:12:58,540 --> 00:13:02,089
I'm on Rowena.

151
00:13:02,089 --> 00:13:07,160
Lamar was a really nice boy.

152
00:13:07,160 --> 00:13:10,089
Marguerite liked him.

153
00:13:10,089 --> 00:13:16,850
Do you want to get a pizza? asked Lamar.

154
00:13:16,850 --> 00:13:21,920
OK, Marguerite answered.

155
00:13:21,920 --> 00:13:24,519
Marguerite called her grandmother.

156
00:13:24,519 --> 00:13:30,370
"I'm getting a pizza with Lamar," she said.

157
00:13:30,370 --> 00:13:33,529
"And he'll walk home with me.

158
00:13:33,529 --> 00:13:37,050
Is that OK?"

159
00:13:37,050 --> 00:13:41,280
The black van was near Rowena Avenue.

160
00:13:41,280 --> 00:13:44,350
The driver was Steemcleena.

161
00:13:44,350 --> 00:13:49,520
Scylla and Morbid were in the back of the
van.

162
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:55,699
"She's out of her house," said Morbid.

163
00:13:55,699 --> 00:13:59,459
He gave the laptop to Scylla.

164
00:13:59,459 --> 00:14:04,860
Scylla wrote a message: Hi Marg.

165
00:14:04,860 --> 00:14:08,139
It's Lamar...

166
00:14:08,139 --> 00:14:10,360
Marguerite answered.

167
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:13,940
Scylla wrote another message.

168
00:14:13,940 --> 00:14:18,990
The van stopped near the pizza restaurant
and waited.

169
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:24,100
Then, they saw Marguerite in the street.

170
00:14:24,100 --> 00:14:27,990
"Go!" shouted Morbid.

171
00:14:27,990 --> 00:14:32,019
Scylla got out of the van.

172
00:14:32,019 --> 00:14:40,899
He pulled a bag over Marguerite's head from
behind, and he and Morbid threw her into the

173
00:14:40,899 --> 00:14:42,540
van.

174
00:14:42,540 --> 00:14:47,230
Steemcleena drove away quickly.

175
00:14:47,230 --> 00:14:51,790
"Help!" shouted Marguerite.

176
00:14:51,790 --> 00:14:54,540
"Be quiet!"

177
00:14:54,540 --> 00:14:56,320
shouted Morbid.

178
00:14:56,320 --> 00:15:01,050
"Maybe you can win the game."

179
00:15:01,050 --> 00:15:03,730
"Win?" asked Marguerite.

180
00:15:03,730 --> 00:15:08,769
"What do you mean?"

181
00:15:08,769 --> 00:15:15,050
Steemcleena stopped the van in a park, with
nobody near.

182
00:15:15,050 --> 00:15:20,490
Morbid and Steemcleena were behind Scylla.

183
00:15:20,490 --> 00:15:25,170
This was Scylla's game.

184
00:15:25,170 --> 00:15:32,970
Marguerite got out of the van quickly, and
she pulled the bag off her head.

185
00:15:32,970 --> 00:15:39,190
She couldn't run away; Steemcleena and Morbid
could stop her.

186
00:15:39,190 --> 00:15:44,600
But she was tall and strong, and ready for
Scylla.

187
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:51,829
Her hand flew out and hit him on the nose.

188
00:15:51,829 --> 00:15:57,930
There was blood on Scylla's face now, and
he was angry.

189
00:15:57,930 --> 00:16:03,800
He ran at her, but she kicked him hard in
the stomach.

190
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:08,240
And then she kicked him again.

191
00:16:08,240 --> 00:16:11,029
Steemcleena looked at Morbid.

192
00:16:11,029 --> 00:16:17,020
"She's too good for Scylla," he said.

193
00:16:17,020 --> 00:16:23,120
He took out a gun and shot Marguerite in the
head.

194
00:16:23,120 --> 00:16:32,440
Then, Scylla put on the gloves and put the
cable around the dead woman's neck.

195
00:16:32,440 --> 00:16:36,610
He took her shoes and put them in the van.

196
00:16:36,610 --> 00:16:42,450
"That wasn't good," said Steemcleena to Scylla.

197
00:16:42,450 --> 00:16:50,870
"But maybe you'll win the next game."

198
00:16:50,870 --> 00:16:57,160
CHAPTER FIVE
Scylla's next game

199
00:16:57,160 --> 00:17:05,270
Justine met Police Lieutenant Nora Cronin
in the park at 4 a.m. on Sunday.

200
00:17:05,270 --> 00:17:10,810
"The Chief of Police is here," said Nora.

201
00:17:10,810 --> 00:17:14,900
"He wants to talk to you."

202
00:17:14,900 --> 00:17:21,500
The Chief was with three police officers near
Marguerite's body.

203
00:17:21,500 --> 00:17:24,220
Justine walked up to him.

204
00:17:24,220 --> 00:17:28,210
"It's good to see you," he said.

205
00:17:28,210 --> 00:17:32,040
"We need your help.

206
00:17:32,040 --> 00:17:34,620
Thirteen women are dead.

207
00:17:34,620 --> 00:17:36,610
And look!

208
00:17:36,610 --> 00:17:44,330
Somebody shot her dead - so why is there cable
around her neck?"

209
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:48,890
"It's very strange," said Justine.

210
00:17:48,890 --> 00:17:53,080
"And where's her handbag?"

211
00:17:53,080 --> 00:18:00,720
"There's no handbag," said the Chief, "and
no shoes.

212
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:03,570
I'm waiting for the email."

213
00:18:03,570 --> 00:18:15,120
On Sunday evening, Scylla was on the terrace
of his apartment, at the top of a tall building.

214
00:18:15,120 --> 00:18:21,780
The city was beautiful at night, but he didn't
look at it.

215
00:18:21,780 --> 00:18:25,580
His face and body were black and blue.

216
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:30,950
"That girl was strong," he thought.

217
00:18:30,950 --> 00:18:36,820
Then, he read the message from Morbid again.

218
00:18:36,820 --> 00:18:40,600
You weren't good yesterday, Scylla.

219
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:43,470
Steemcleena isn't happy.

220
00:18:43,470 --> 00:18:47,760
But you can play again tonight.

221
00:18:47,760 --> 00:18:50,370
We have someone for you.

222
00:18:50,370 --> 00:18:56,080
Be ready at 7 p.m.

223
00:18:56,080 --> 00:19:04,170
Morbid and Steemcleena were at the door now,
and Scylla went to open it.

224
00:19:04,170 --> 00:19:09,760
"How's the nose?" asked Morbid.

225
00:19:09,760 --> 00:19:12,000
OK, said Scylla.

226
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,460
"Do you want a drink?"

227
00:19:15,460 --> 00:19:18,840
"No," said Steemcleena.

228
00:19:18,840 --> 00:19:21,730
"Let's go on the terrace.

229
00:19:21,730 --> 00:19:26,550
I want to show you something."

230
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:33,070
The three men walked on to the terrace and
looked down at the city.

231
00:19:33,070 --> 00:19:37,890
Then, Steemcleena turned to Scylla.

232
00:19:37,890 --> 00:19:43,170
"You think you can play again?" he asked.

233
00:19:43,170 --> 00:19:45,230
"You can.

234
00:19:45,230 --> 00:19:50,570
But you're playing with us."

235
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:59,350
Steemcleena took Scylla's legs, and Morbid
took his arms, and they threw him over the

236
00:19:59,350 --> 00:20:03,260
terrace wall.

237
00:20:03,260 --> 00:20:08,470
Justine and Jack were at Private with Mo-bot.

238
00:20:08,470 --> 00:20:10,660
They talked about Marguerite.

239
00:20:10,660 --> 00:20:19,890
"The killer sent an email," said Justine,
"and we found her shoes.

240
00:20:19,890 --> 00:20:25,310
Sci is looking at them now, but they're probably
clean."

241
00:20:25,310 --> 00:20:35,670
"The killer is using a van to look for the
young women, I think," said Mo-bot.

242
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:47,650
"He has a laptop and a radio in the van, and
he can send messages to the women's cell phones.

243
00:20:47,650 --> 00:20:54,030
He can stop messages to their phones from
other people, too.

244
00:20:54,030 --> 00:21:00,910
And maybe he can find them in the street from
their phones."

245
00:21:00,910 --> 00:21:05,720
"Is that possible?" asked Jack.

246
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:07,970
"I don't know.

247
00:21:07,970 --> 00:21:12,700
I'll ask Sci about it," said Mo-bot.

