The two women went into the bar after him.

500
00:41:21,200 --> 00:41:25,290
There were a lot of people in the bar.

501
00:41:25,290 --> 00:41:29,800
Crocker was in the corner with a man with
long hair.

502
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:34,260
Justine bought drinks, and the two women watched.

503
00:41:34,260 --> 00:41:41,380
Half an hour later, the men finished their
drinks and left.

504
00:41:41,380 --> 00:41:49,290
Nora and Justine quickly went to the men's
table and took the glasses.

505
00:41:49,290 --> 00:41:57,770
In the car, Justine called Sci. "Can you meet
us at Private in twenty minutes?"

506
00:41:57,770 --> 00:41:58,770
she asked.

507
00:41:58,770 --> 00:42:03,440
"We have some DNA for you!"

508
00:42:03,440 --> 00:42:14,280
Late on Wednesday, Jack and Emilio drove back
to the city from the Agoura Hills.

509
00:42:14,280 --> 00:42:21,230
Jack left Emilio at his apartment and went
to see Andy Cushman.

510
00:42:21,230 --> 00:42:25,340
"Jack, why are you here now?

511
00:42:25,340 --> 00:42:27,250
It's 1 a.m.

512
00:42:27,250 --> 00:42:31,120
You look tired!" said Andy.

513
00:42:31,120 --> 00:42:35,640
"I am tired," said Jack.

514
00:42:35,640 --> 00:42:40,250
"Today, I drove to the Agoura Hills.

515
00:42:40,250 --> 00:42:47,560
How much did you pay Bo Montgomery to kill
Shelby?"

516
00:42:47,560 --> 00:42:50,250
Andy started to cry.

517
00:42:50,250 --> 00:42:55,310
"You don't understand, Jack," he said.

518
00:42:55,310 --> 00:43:01,620
"She was with another man, that movie star.

519
00:43:01,620 --> 00:43:05,110
I couldn't live with that!"

520
00:43:05,110 --> 00:43:09,480
Jack didn't speak.

521
00:43:09,480 --> 00:43:17,390
He hit Andy in the face, three times, and
left.

522
00:43:17,390 --> 00:43:23,360
CHAPTER ELEVEN
A dark blue van

523
00:43:23,360 --> 00:43:30,020
The next morning, Sci had news for Justine
and Nora about the DNA.

524
00:43:30,020 --> 00:43:36,210
"I have DNA from one of the glasses," he said.

525
00:43:36,210 --> 00:43:40,100
"Not Crocker's glass, the other man's.

526
00:43:40,100 --> 00:43:45,860
It's the same as the DNA on Wendy Borman's
clothes."

527
00:43:45,860 --> 00:43:51,920
"Who is this other man?" asked Justine.

528
00:43:51,920 --> 00:43:54,960
"We don't know him.

529
00:43:54,960 --> 00:43:57,630
Is it Morbid?"

530
00:43:57,630 --> 00:43:59,150
"Maybe.

531
00:43:59,150 --> 00:44:02,250
And what did you get from Crocker's glass?"

532
00:44:02,250 --> 00:44:04,570
Nora asked Sci.

533
00:44:04,570 --> 00:44:08,750
"I couldn't get DNA from Crocker's glass.

534
00:44:08,750 --> 00:44:13,690
It was too dirty," said Sci.

535
00:44:13,690 --> 00:44:16,110
Justine looked at Nora.

536
00:44:16,110 --> 00:44:18,270
"What now?"

537
00:44:18,270 --> 00:44:19,550
she asked.

538
00:44:19,550 --> 00:44:25,370
"We must find Crocker!" said Nora.

539
00:44:25,370 --> 00:44:33,710
Mo-bot worked all morning on her computer,
and then she found something.

540
00:44:33,710 --> 00:44:35,740
She called Jack.

541
00:44:35,740 --> 00:44:40,180
"Morbid wants to kill Graciella tonight!

542
00:44:40,180 --> 00:44:45,850
He's sending her text messages from a friend,
Lulu.

543
00:44:45,850 --> 00:44:50,370
Graciella is answering these messages from
Lulu.

544
00:44:50,370 --> 00:44:58,670
She says, 'See you after school', but I don't
know where they are meeting."

545
00:44:58,670 --> 00:45:04,040
"Where is Morbid?" asked Jack.

546
00:45:04,040 --> 00:45:10,420
"I don't know," said Mo-bot.

547
00:45:10,420 --> 00:45:16,590
Justine and Nora drove to Crocker's office
on Wilshire Boulevard.

548
00:45:16,590 --> 00:45:24,930
"Mr. Crocker is on vacation today," said the
woman at the desk.

549
00:45:24,930 --> 00:45:30,060
They drove fast to his apartment, but he wasn't
there.

550
00:45:30,060 --> 00:45:35,300
"Let's find his van!" said Nora.

551
00:45:35,300 --> 00:45:38,100
Nora called the police station.

552
00:45:38,100 --> 00:45:44,710
"We're looking for a new, dark blue Toyota
van.

553
00:45:44,710 --> 00:45:48,460
Every police car must look for it."

554
00:45:48,460 --> 00:45:56,390
Then, she and Justine waited in their car
near Crocker's apartment building.

555
00:45:56,390 --> 00:45:59,290
The call came back to Nora.

556
00:45:59,290 --> 00:46:04,670
"The dark blue van is in Silver Lake.

557
00:46:04,670 --> 00:46:09,070
It was on Alvarado Street, but we can't find
it now."

558
00:46:09,070 --> 00:46:13,600
"We must stop that van!"

559
00:46:13,600 --> 00:46:15,900
shouted Nora into the radio.

560
00:46:15,900 --> 00:46:20,790
"The driver is a killer!"

561
00:46:20,790 --> 00:46:24,130
Jack and Emilio were on the road, too.

562
00:46:24,130 --> 00:46:26,510
Mo-bot called Jack.

563
00:46:26,510 --> 00:46:33,590
"I'm reading more messages from Morbid to
Graciella," she told him.

564
00:46:33,590 --> 00:46:39,520
"She's in Glendale, and he wants to meet at
Ralph's Supermarket."

565
00:46:39,520 --> 00:46:46,440
Graciella was in the street near the supermarket.

566
00:46:46,440 --> 00:46:49,280
Morbid walked up to her.

567
00:46:49,280 --> 00:46:51,840
"Graciella?" he said.

568
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:55,460
"I'm a friend of Lulu's.

569
00:46:55,460 --> 00:46:57,680
She's in hospital.

570
00:46:57,680 --> 00:47:01,190
Can you come with me to visit her?

571
00:47:01,190 --> 00:47:04,740
She wants to see you."

572
00:47:04,740 --> 00:47:09,210
Morbid put his hand on Graciella's arm.

573
00:47:09,210 --> 00:47:15,870
Jack ran across the street and hit him in
the stomach.

574
00:47:15,870 --> 00:47:19,900
Morbid fell down, and Jack held him.

575
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:22,860
"Where's Rudolph Crocker?"

576
00:47:22,860 --> 00:47:25,600
shouted Jack.

577
00:47:25,600 --> 00:47:30,910
Nora and Justine got to Glendale quickly,
too.

578
00:47:30,910 --> 00:47:37,180
Crocker's van was behind the supermarket,
with a police car next to it.

579
00:47:37,180 --> 00:47:40,610
Nora talked to a police officer.

580
00:47:40,610 --> 00:47:44,990
"Crocker is in the van, Lieutenant," he said.

581
00:47:44,990 --> 00:47:48,690
"He won't open the doors."

582
00:47:48,690 --> 00:47:52,020
Justine walked up to the van.

583
00:47:52,020 --> 00:47:55,000
Crocker was sitting with his hands on his
head.

584
00:47:55,000 --> 00:48:00,810
"Get out of the van, Crocker," she said.

585
00:48:00,810 --> 00:48:03,550
He smiled at her.

586
00:48:03,550 --> 00:48:08,640
Justine hit the van window hard with her gun.

587
00:48:08,640 --> 00:48:15,930
She put her hand into the van, opened the
door, and pulled Crocker out.

588
00:48:15,930 --> 00:48:20,910
There was blood and glass everywhere.

589
00:48:20,910 --> 00:48:26,250
At the supermarket, the police took Morbid
away.

590
00:48:26,250 --> 00:48:30,420
Jack and Emilio walked to Crocker's van.

591
00:48:30,420 --> 00:48:35,380
They found Justine with her foot on Crocker's
back.

592
00:48:35,380 --> 00:48:39,150
"Are you OK?" asked Jack.

593
00:48:39,150 --> 00:48:42,460
"There's a lot of blood on you."

594
00:48:42,460 --> 00:48:48,050
"It's not mine," said Justine.

595
00:48:48,050 --> 00:48:50,750
"It's Crocker's."

596
00:48:50,750 --> 00:48:56,230
Jack put some glass with blood on it in a
bag and gave it to Emilio.

597
00:48:56,230 --> 00:49:00,119
"Get this to Sci," he said.

598
00:49:00,119 --> 00:49:03,750
"There's DNA here."

599
00:49:03,750 --> 00:49:06,850
The police took Crocker away.

600
00:49:06,850 --> 00:49:08,960
Justine looked at Nora.

601
00:49:08,960 --> 00:49:16,910
"We need to go to his apartment and look for
Wendy Borman's necklace."

602
00:49:16,910 --> 00:49:22,560
Justine and Nora looked everywhere in Crocker's
apartment.

603
00:49:22,560 --> 00:49:25,060
They found nothing.

604
00:49:25,060 --> 00:49:31,340
Justine opened the closet in the bedroom to
look at Crocker's clothes again.

605
00:49:31,340 --> 00:49:37,340
The light was on a string, and she pulled
it.

606
00:49:37,340 --> 00:49:42,170
She looked at the end of the string in her
hand.

607
00:49:42,170 --> 00:49:45,890
It was the star from Wendy's necklace.

608
00:49:45,890 --> 00:49:54,230
"We've caught them, Justine," said Jack, back
at Private.

609
00:49:54,230 --> 00:49:59,140
"Sci looked at the DNA from Crocker's blood.

610
00:49:59,140 --> 00:50:05,360
It's the same as the DNA from Wendy's clothes."

611
00:50:05,360 --> 00:50:10,310
The next morning, Jack's phone woke him early.

612
00:50:10,310 --> 00:50:14,240
"Jack, it's Carmine Noccia.

613
00:50:14,240 --> 00:50:18,000
I have some bad news for you.

614
00:50:18,000 --> 00:50:23,140
Your friend Andy Cushman is dead.

615
00:50:23,140 --> 00:50:29,020
His car went off the road near Marin, and
it went into the ocean."

616
00:50:29,020 --> 00:50:36,990
"Did anybody see Andy's car go into the ocean?"
said Jack.

617
00:50:36,990 --> 00:50:39,869
"Oh, yes.

618
00:50:39,869 --> 00:50:42,680
One of my cousins saw it.

619
00:50:42,680 --> 00:50:46,430
He was the only person there.

620
00:50:46,430 --> 00:50:51,750
Have a good day," said Carmine.

621
00:50:51,750 --> 00:51:00,100
Jack looked at his phone for a minute and
thought, "Carmine's cousin killed Andy."

622
00:51:00,100 --> 00:51:05,710
Then, he turned and threw it out of the window.

623
00:51:05,710 --> 00:51:10,320
It was time for a new phone and a new phone
number.

624
00:51:10,320 --> 00:51:10,970
- THE END -

